<%# Phase 7.5 §11b — banner row.
    Renders the cached banner image when `banner_url` is present.
    Per locked decision (LOCK 3) the row is HIDDEN entirely when
    `banner_url` is nil — no colored placeholder, no empty block.
    Once ChannelSync populates `banner_url` (Phase 8) the row appears.

    2026-05-11 (later) — banner geometry was retuned to match
    YouTube's channel-header aspect ratio (~6.2:1) so the detail
    pane reads like the source layout. The `.channel-banner`
    class owns the box (`aspect-ratio`, `border-radius`,
    `overflow: hidden`) and the inner `<img>` covers it. Inline
    `max-height: 200px` was dropped — `aspect-ratio` is now the
    single source of truth for the banner's vertical size.

    Phase 7.5 §11f — the banner upload flow on the edit page uses
    a Turbo Stream to replace `#channel-banner-section` after a
    successful submit. This partial stays render-once on the show
    page; the section wrapper is owned by the edit / show callers.
%>
<% if channel.banner_url.present? %>
  <div class="channel-banner">
    <%= image_tag channel.banner_url, alt: "channel banner" %>
  </div>
<% end %>
